{{Refimprove|date=February 2010}}

[[Amateur boxing]] has been practised in [[Mongolia]] since 1948 and Mongolia national amateur boxing team consists of 27 boxers.<ref>[http://www.olloo.mn/modules.php?name=News&file=print&sid=108135 <U+0414>.<U+0411><U+0430><U+0442><U+043C><U+0454><U+043D><U+0445>: <U+0410><U+043D><U+0445> <U+0434><U+044D><U+044D><U+043B><U+0442><U+044D><U+0439>, <U+043C><U+043E><U+043D><U+0433><U+043E><U+043B> <U+0433><U+0443><U+0442><U+0430><U+043B><U+0442><U+0430><U+0439> <U+0431><U+043E><U+043A><U+0441> <U+0442><U+043E><U+0433><U+043B><U+043E><U+0434><U+043E><U+0433> <U+0431><U+0430><U+0439><U+043B><U+0430><U+0430>]</ref> Mongolian national amateur boxing athletes represents Mongolia in regional, [[Asian Games|continental]] and [[Olympics|world]] tournaments and matches sanctioned by the [[Amateur International Boxing Association]] (AIBA). Mongolian olympic boxing national team was founded in 1960.[[People's Republic of Mongolia|Communist government]] of Mongolia banned boxing, however, the government  ended ban on boxing soon. [[Professional boxing]] began in Mongolia in the 1990s.

==Achievements==

===[[Summer Olympics]]===
{{Main|Boxing at the Summer Olympics}}
Mongolian boxers first participated at the Olympic Games in [[Mongolia at the 1972 Summer Olympics|1972]].

====2004 Athens Olympics====
{{Main|Boxing at the 2004 Summer Olympics}}
[[Uranchimegiin M<U+00F6>nkh-Erdene]] represented Mongolia in this edition of the [[Summer Olympics]]. He won his first bout but was defeated in the second.

